%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Phi+Kappa+Phi+Forum&amp;rft.atitle=It+Was+I+Who+Did+It%3A+Women%27s+Role+in+the+Founding+of+the+Nation&amp;rft.volume=86&amp;rft.pages=16&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.aulast=Berkin&amp;rft.aufirst=Carol&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASpinning+bee\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Macdonald, Anne (1988). <i>No Idle Hands: The Social History of American Knitting</i>. New York: Ballatine Books. pp.&#160;80\u201381.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=No+Idle+Hands%3A+The+Social+History+of+American+Knitting&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pages=80-81&amp;rft.pub=Ballatine+Books&amp;rft.date=1988&amp;rft.aulast=Macdonald&amp;rft.aufirst=Anne&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASpinning+bee\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Applewhite, Harriet B. (1993). <i>Women and Politics in the Age of Democratic Revolution</i>. Ann Arbor: University of Michigan Press. p.&#160;197.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Women+and+Politics+in+the+Age+of+Democratic+Revolution&amp;rft.place=Ann+Arbor&amp;rft.pages=197&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Michigan+Press&amp;rft.date=1993&amp;rft.aulast=Applewhite&amp;rft.aufirst=Harriet+B.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASpinning+bee\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Peskin, Lawrence (2003). <i>Manufacturing Revolution: The Intellectual Origins of Early American Industry</i>. Baltimore: Johns Hopkins University Press. pp.&#160;10\u201311.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Manufacturing+Revolution%3A+The+Intellectual+Origins+of+Early+American+Industry&amp;rft.place=Baltimore&amp;rft.pages=10-11&amp;rft.pub=Johns+Hopkins+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.aulast=Peskin&amp;rft.aufirst=Lawrence&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASpinning+bee\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Ulrich, Laurel Thatcher (1998). \"Wheels, Looms, and the Gendered Divisions of Labor in Eighteenth Century New England\". <i>The William and Mary Quarterly</i>. <b>55</b>: 9  &#8211; via EBSCOhost.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+William+and+Mary+Quarterly&amp;rft.atitle=Wheels%2C+Looms%2C+and+the+Gendered+Divisions+of+Labor+in+Eighteenth+Century+New+England&amp;rft.volume=55&amp;rft.pages=9&amp;rft.date=1998&amp;rft.aulast=Ulrich&amp;rft.aufirst=Laurel+Thatcher&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASpinning+bee\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2216\nCached time: 20180912161110\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.096 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.125 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 412/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 9734/2097152 bytes\nTemplate ar